<tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><img border="0" src="../triangle.JPG"><font size="3" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>DRUID MED KITING GIANTS IN FRONTIER MOUNTAINS</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Group / Solo:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Solo - Druid</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Mob Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">24 to 33</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Zone:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Frontier Mountains</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Location:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Giant Fortress</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Character Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">34 to 39</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Strategy:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">I have found a quick and easy way for kiting Giants in the Frontier Mountains zone.  The Giant Fort is always well camped with quite a few groups pulling out of it.  This makes for pulling single giants out easy.
<br><br>
The plan: find the giant you want to pull.  I usually try to pull Tumps or better since Hillocks are lower in level and some are green.  Also, I've heard that Tumps drop the Forest Loop more often than any other giant.
<br><br>
I pull with the Combust spell (29th level direct damage).  It is hardly fully resisted, so it does at least some damage, typically the full 182 points.  With the giant hot on your tail, run out of the fort to the left.  Make sure the giant gets out of the fort.  If you cut off the wall too quickly, it might get stuck inside the fort, which could pull a lot more giants.  Run down the right side of the fort.  If you're looking at the entrance of the fort, go to the right - it is the corner closest to the entrance, over a small hill towards a large rock outcropping near the back of the fort.  At this point, close to the middle of this flat section, Ensnare the giant and then run a little farther and cast Ensnaring Roots.  Once rooted, hit the giant with both DoTs, Immolate and Drones of Doom.  Then sit and med.
<br><br>
The DoTs last 60 seconds and a full root lasts for close to 90 seconds.  When both DoTs wear off, hit the giant again with Drones of Doom.  The reason for this is even though the root will wear off halfway through the DoT duration, you will get half the damage of the DoT for less mana than casting Combust or Fury of Air.  It appears to be more mana efficient.  When the root breaks, you can kite the giant until the DoT wears off.  Remember, with the new snare/root rules, the giant will still be snared, or blast it once with Combust or Fury of Air.  In either case, the giant will be sufficiently damaged to start running.  I typically melee at this point because I'm gaining mana back while meleeing.  In the minute or so I use to melee, I wouldn't gain the mana back medding as fast.  You could probably use a lower level spell, but I haven't tried that yet.
<br><br>
There are some concerns with this method.  First, if Ensnare is resisted, it creates problems.  This side of the fort, however, is a long nearly flat section with no wandering mobs.  You can kite quite a bit to a hill with a single tree and then back towards the fort until Ensnare lands.  If Ensnaring Roots is resisted or breaks early, again, you can kite to the tree and around it back to the fort until it does stick for a sufficient amount of time.
<br><br>
The second problem is when pulling one giant at a time.  Usually, this isn't a problem because most giants are single pulls or another group has already pulled one away leaving one by itself.  If, however, there are 2 very close by, I usually Ensnare the one I don't want (typically a Hillock) which pulls the one I do.  In pulling the other giant out and away from the fort, you outrun the Ensnared giant and it loses interest in you.  Pay attention to the faction hits to make sure another group kills it.  I have not encountered a problem with this method.
<br><br>
At level 34, I use between 2 and 3 bubbles of mana, closer to just 2, which minimizes the downtime.  I also gain a little over a half a blue bubble per kill and can take between 3 and 4 giants per hour.  The last time I soloed like this I was trading SoW for clarity with an Enchanter and in approximately 2 hours of gaming time, I netted over a bubble of experience.  Are there better places that are more efficient?  Probably.  So far, this has been enjoyable and not tedious.  It is a strategy worth looking into if you've hit a rut.
<br><br>
DreamerZ<br>
aka Kallie Natureswrath, 34 druid<br>
Mith Marr</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Author:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">DreamerZ (Mithaniel Marr)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rating:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>6.9</b> (average of <b>18</b> votes)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rate this spot:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><FORM ACTION = "ratehg.asp" METHOD = post><SELECT NAME="Voting"><OPTION VALUE="0">Rate this Spot</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="1">1 - Don't even bother</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="2">2</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="3">3</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="4">4</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="5">5 - It is ok</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="6">6</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="7">7</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="8">8</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="9">9</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="10">10 - You must come here</OPTION></SELECT><INPUT TYPE = "hidden" NAME = "intHGID" VALUE = 52><INPUT TYPE = "submit" VALUE="Rate It!"></form></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><div align="cente